{
  "texts": [
    "While relying solely on text for communication not only hampers the efficiency of the interaction but also slows the pace of learning Auslan.Consequently, an urgent need for software capable of recognising and translating Auslan is evident.",
    "Such technology is pivotal for enabling non-signers to quickly comprehend the messages of Auslan signers, thereby facilitating both communication and Auslan education.",
    "To address this, we have developed an app, called Interactive Auslan Communication at Home (IACH).",
    "This APP is specifically designed to facilitate communication between Auslan signers and non-signers, with tailored features for scenarios involving parents and children.",
    "Our IACH provides three functions, text-to-sign lookup, sign-to-text translation, and Auslan selfteaching respectively, serving as a bridge for communication within PODCs and CODAs families."
  ]
}